TITLE: University of Virginia manhunt: Who is ex-football player shooting suspect Christopher Darnell Jones, Jr?
SUMMARY: Law enforcement are pouring over the University of Virginia campus in Charlottesville for student shooting suspect Christopher Darnell Jones, Jr., as classes are canceled Monday.

TITLE: Buster Murdaugh living in South Carolina ahead of father's murder trial: exclusive pics
SUMMARY: Buster Murdaugh is holed up at his girlfriend's apartment in Hilton Head as the South Carolina murder trial of his jailed and disbarred father, Alex Murdaugh, draws near.

TITLE: Police name suspect in university shooting, GOP flips key district in battle for House and more top headlines
SUMMARY: CAMPUS SHOOTING - Police name former football player as suspect in University of Virginia shooting that killed 3 and left 2 injured

TITLE: Florida woman arrested after drugs seized from motel room, 'armed and dangerous' man at large
SUMMARY: A woman was arrested after a search for a wanted man at a motel room turned into a drug bust. Police are still looking for the man who is considered to be 'armed and dangerous.'

TITLE: Virginia man taken into custody after fatally shooting dog
SUMMARY: A Virginia man is in custody after he shot and killed a dog during a verbal altercation with its owner. He is charged with animal cruelty and is being held without bond.

TITLE: University of Virginia shooting kills 3, injures 2; former football player named as suspect
SUMMARY: A shooting was reported on campus at the University of Virginia in Charlottesville Sunday night. UVA police named former football player Christopher Darnell Jones Jr. as the suspect.

TITLE: Texas DPS apprehends 19 illegal immigrants from human smuggling attempts, stash house
SUMMARY: Texas authorities arrested nineteen illegal immigrants after multiple traffic stops and a stash house revealed human smuggling attempts. They have been referred to U.S. Border Patrol.

TITLE: Twitter to allow organizations identify associated accounts
SUMMARY: Elon Musk said on Sunday that Twitter will soon allow organizations to identify which Twitter accounts are associated with them, also giving them permission to remove accounts.

TITLE: New York man busted with 20k fentanyl pills released without bail
SUMMARY: New York City resident Manuel Pagan was arrested after he was found with about 20,000 multicolored fentanyl pills. He was then released without bail and placed under supervision.

TITLE: Teachers union tweet claims educators know 'better than anyone' what kids need to 'learn and thrive'
SUMMARY: The National Education Association tweeted Saturday that educators have their students' best interest in mind and know better than anyone what they need to succeed.
